2:T4b4,{"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"FAQPage","mainEntity":[{"@type":"Question","name":"What is the difference between an AI support agent and a chatbot?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Traditional chatbots follow scripted decision trees — they can only respond to queries they were explicitly programmed for. AI support agents use large language models to understand natural language, access live data, and resolve issues they were not specifically trained on."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"What is a typical resolution rate for AI customer support agents?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Resolution rates vary by use case. Simple, high-volume queries (order tracking, password resets, FAQs) can see 60-80% autonomous resolution. Complex technical or emotional support queries typically require human escalation."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Can AI support agents handle refunds and order changes?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes — the more capable AI support agents integrate with your order management system and can execute actions like processing refunds, updating shipping addresses, or cancelling subscriptions, subject to rules you define."}}]}5:["slug","what-is-an-ai-customer-support-agent","d"]
